   Schedule 
  
     
     
       The following list of topics and corresponding readings is subject
      to change. All readings refer to the textbook: K. H. Rosen, 
        Discrete Mathematics and its Applications  , Fourth Edition, McGraw-Hill, 1995.
       
      Homework assignments will be available starting each Tuesday in weeks 1--9.
      There will be a quiz in lecture on Thursday in weeks 2, 3, 4, 5, 7, 8, 9, 10.
           Week 1.  Introduction to the course:  Logic (1.1 -1.3); Sets (1.4)  
         Week 2.  Set operations (1.5) Counting basics (4.1, 4.2)  
         Week 3. Permutation and combinations (4.3, 4.6)  
         Week 4. Probability (4.4, 4.5, handouts)  
         Week 5. Probability cont. (4.4,4.5, handouts)   
         Week 6. Methods of proof (3.1);   Midterm,   ; Thursday, November 2nd, in class  
         Week 7.  Mathematical induction (3.2)  
         Week 8. Sequence and summation (1.7); Review of logarithms (A.1);
          Recursive definitions (3.3) 
         Week 9. Setting up recurrence relations ( 5.1)  
         Week 10.  Solving recurrence relations (5.1,5.2 through page 323)  
         Week 11.  Final Exam  Tuesday, December 5 
            
     



       
